1 — Slide 1: Evidence Workflow
(unchanged — slides describe capabilities, no V1/V2 issue)

"First layer — evidence workflow. The headline: continuous evidence, without continuous chasing."
"Eight capabilities, organized two ways. The top row is automation — paths where evidence flows in without human action. System-to-system integration pulls directly from source systems where evidence already lives. Carry-forward respects what's still valid. Freshness windows notify before evidence ages out. AI Copilot reads the uploaded file with the reviewer."
"The bottom row is how the work reaches humans when judgment is required. Power Automate sends a targeted email. The Control Owner Portal shows only their open requests. Upload is drag-and-drop. Approval leaves an auditable trail."
"What this replaces — owners hunting through email for what's theirs, re-collecting evidence that hasn't aged, finding gaps reactively instead of proactively."

