11 — Wireframe C: Evidence Record Populated
(12_Wireframe_C_Evidence_Populated.html)

"And here's a direction for how an evidence record looks after collection and acceptance. CPROC-0010 on Application 0007. Status, Provided. File in SharePoint, indexed by control and application. Submitted by the Control Owner. Reviewed by the Auditor. All locked."
"But the wow is at the bottom — Snapshot at Collection. Eight fields, frozen at the moment evidence was submitted. The control title. The application's owning business unit. Its hosting type. Its criticality. Its SOX flag."
"If the source system changes any of these tomorrow, this snapshot doesn't move. The audit record always shows what the world looked like when evidence was collected. That's the immutability story made concrete."

~38 sec

12 — Slide 3: Governance
(unchanged)

"Third layer — governance. The guardrails. The headline: tamper-proof by design."
"Three protections. The records can't be hand-edited — master data is locked to source. The platform refuses invalid states — gates can't reverse, cycles can't half-close, evidence flows one direction. And today's record is also tomorrow's record — every snapshot preserved, append-only history."
"No one — not a panicked Control Owner, not an over-eager Risk Manager, not a malicious actor — can quietly move evidence around the system. That's what makes the platform audit-grade."

~33 sec
